Description: Adrian Rubin LLC is the proprietary real estate development venture launched by Adrian Rubin, and is based in Philadelphia, PA.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Philadelphia Area, Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: Adrian Rubin LLC is a Philadelphia - based venture owned and operated by Adrian Rubin. This company has served as the primary enterprise under which Adrian and his associates have conducted business for nearly thirty years. Adrian Rubin LLC is known all over the country as a premiere real estate development firm, and has a reputation for not only getting the job done well, but for housing a team that spends time getting to really understand the wants and needs of the client while managing the project in an organized and efficient manner.  Adrian Rubin LLC is fully committed to the power of communication and the knows that creating a strong, supportive and talented team is that comes together with the client is absolutely critical to the success of a new property. This firm is known for not only building amazing spaces, but for putting the time and effort into building relationships with the clients. The purpose of this is to not only make sure that the entire team is on the same page with the vision of the project, but it's so that the client has an incredible experience with this firm during what can otherwise be a very stressful and time-consuming endeavor. Clear communication and an expectation of transparency have always been two key factors in the Adrian Rubin LLC approach, and this coupled with traditional hard work and follow through have led not only to the successful execution of these projects, but also to continued professional relationships with the clients time and time again.  Adrian Rubin LLC currently deals with residential property development deals, but has a proven track record with commercial development as well. From shopping centers to office buildings to smaller housing complexes for new families, Adrian Rubin LLC is adept at addressing the needs and demands of the client while offering transparency and solutions to the spaces currently available in that market. Although Adrian Rubin LLC is based in Philadelphia, PA, the company has visited every region of the country in order to create beautiful functional properties that exceed the expectations of the client, and provide a wonderful experience for those who ultimately end up living in and using the space.  Since its first inception, Adrian Rubin LLC was created with the intention of creating a business that provided the network and support necessary to successfully execute large-scale real estate development deals. Over the past thirty years, Adrian Rubin LLC has shown itself to be more than capable of that initial objective, and has hundreds of satisfied clients and customers who strongly agree.

Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: Chris Chickering is a psychotherapist, recording artist, bestselling author, speaker, trainer, and social entrepreneur passionate about helping people build upon their inner strengths, break through barriers, and fulfill their untapped potential. Chris is known for his collaborative, respectful approach, entertaining presentation style, and infectious enthusiasm for whatever he is doing, Chris delivers trainings and presentations, and provides solution-focused coaching and therapy for individuals, couples, families, and groups. As a speaker and trainer, Chris often uses humor and sleight-of-hand magic to educate, entertain, and engage. His presentation topics include Solution-Focused Brief Therapy, Leadership, Leadership Development, Mental Health Ethics, Personal Growth, Business Development, Archetypal Psychology, and Cognitive Behavioral Therapy. As a singer-songwriter, recording artist, and musician, Chris’ musical mission is to write and perform songs that uplift, unite, and inspire. He has a highly regarded body of work you can preview here, on Chris’ Official Music Site, and anywhere music is sold or streamed. Chris Chickering’s #1 bestselling books Next Level Your Life and Persistence, Pivots and Game Changers are available free on Chris’ site (PDF downloads), and for purchase on Amazon. (Next Level…) (Persistence, Pivots…) These personal development books bring you story after story of transformation and growth from Phil Collen of Def Leppard, Actor Glenn Morshower, Amberly Lago, Chris Chickering, Marques Ogden, Robert Helms, Russell Gray, and many more. Chris holds an MA in Counseling with certifications and training in Solution-focused Brief Therapy, EMDR, NLP, hypnosis, accelerated learning, cognitive-behavioral therapy, dialectical behavioral therapy, mindfulness-based stress reduction, motivational interviewing, addiction recovery, and advanced leadership training with Tony Robbins. Prior to becoming a mental health professional, he served as an EMT/Firefighter, television marketing executive, and director of business development for a premiere provider of self-improvement, education, and health programs. In 2007, Chris Chickering founded Guru Authority, an online affiliate marketing agency that helped A-List personal and professional growth experts increase their profits and reach through lucrative joint venture partnerships. A few of Chris’ clients include Jack Canfield, Bob Proctor, Russell Brunson, and Brian Tracy. In this role, he served as an agent and trusted advisor, curating over 300 relevant, high-quality, self-improvement programs for his clients to share with their lists, while connecting hundreds of thousands of everyday people with extraordinary resources to help them live the lives they deserve. Chris grew up in San Francisco. He enjoys high-intensity interval training, hiking in the mountains of his hometown, Santa Fe, New Mexico, and migrating to warm-weather locations in winter.

Description: River Ecosystem is the center of the Frontier Technology startup ecosystem.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: River Ecosystem LLC, founded in September 2016 by Mike Rothenberg and Nick Canafax, is based out of San Francisco and is known the "bridge to Silicon Valley".  River Ecosystem is known world-wide for operating the world's first and most successful accelerator program for early-stage frontier technology startups, the River Accelerator.  River Ecosystem also offers the River Lounge, River Network, and River Partners programs as part of its wholistic approach to helping startups grow and succeed. The River Accelerator program is a 12-week program over a 4-month period where a select group of no more than 10-15 exceptional startups receive mentorship, training, and access.   River Accelerator startup founders receive membership in the exclusive River Network program, where they can access to Silicon Valley's most connected investors, advisors, founders and luminaries.  River Accelerator startups also receive membership in the River Lounge, and access to River Partners who provide funding, advice, and support. River Ecosystem hosts events around the year through the exclusive River Network club, where startup founders receive access to the most connected investors, advisors, founders and luminaries in Silicon Valley through frequent and iconic high-value networking events.  The River Network's most popular event is Founder Field Day, held annually at AT&T Park with the most recent event - Founder Field Day 2017 - held in November 2017. River Ecosystem builds community year-round and provides a bridge to Silicon Valley via the River Lounge at 1062 Folsom, in the heart of the South of Market neighborhood in San Francisco.  Through the River Lounge, startups receive coworking space and and access to River Network events like Founder Field Day.

Description: 511 Capital is a hybrid between an entrepreneurial startup incubator and a private equity firm.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: 511 Capital is a hybrid between an entrepreneurial startup incubator and a private equity firm. 511 Capital lives in a space somewhere between “startup foundry” and private equity-style portfolio management. Always, the company looks for novel and competitively sustainable revenue opportunities - and then build branded portfolio companies to enter those spaces. 511 Capital doesn't work with people that want to start businesses like a typical incubator would – the company hatches out the ideas and bring them to life ourselves. For the first few years of its existence, the focus has been developing consumer durables and building the back-end manufacturing capability to manifest new consumer product visions. With offices and operational facilities in Chicago, Illinois and Shenzhen, China, the business is functioning as a mini-multinational. This global spread of talent lets us act as a “global business accelerator,” bringing substantial levels of design, sourcing and manufacturing talent to our array of startup projects. Mr. Russell Potterfield, founder and CEO of 511 Capital, led his former company, Battenfeld Technologies, Inc., through almost a decade of rapid growth. In 2012, he and the other shareholders in the business sold the business to a private equity firm. The private equity group later sold the business to Smith and Wesson, SWHC. For Mr. Potterfield, the great challenge – and opportunity – from the sale was the loss of the capabilities on the management team that had helped build the Battenfeld business. The structure of 511 Capital allows the management team the opportunity to develop, buy, and sell operating entities without having to re-talent the entire organization. The business model allows a full measure of single-entity entrepreneurial longevity as well as private equity’s enviable ability to maximize the value of an individual company when market conditions warrant a sale. 511 Capital’s first set of startups clearly demonstrates the incubator’s product development chops. More companies are in late-stage development, and more companies are in the evaluation stage. 511 Capital intends on scheduling launches of two to four new “front ends” a year while investing resources to grow each of the existing front ends.

Description: Lexidyne is a recognized leader in applying simulation technology to solve business problems.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: Lexidyne helps clients address and answer specific questions about how a complex future is likely to unfold under various scenarios. When developing simulations, they take a robust, multifaceted approach - define the issues, formulate model structure, and collect/analyze associated data. This approach provides clients with a risk-free virtualization to identify leverage points, test various strategies, and understand the return on investment. Lexidyne integrates a system dynamics conceptual framework with discrete-event and agent-based models. The system dynamics framework facilitates a common conceptualization of the structure of a system, while the discrete-event and agent-based simulation methods represent individual entities with distinct attributes and behaviors and the interaction between these entities. This approach provides a nuanced perspective on complex systems, allowing their clients to craft customized strategies tailored to specific populations rather than relying on aggregate measures.
